We should note here that the main contribution to the absorption mechanism comes from the plasmonic losses in the two metals. On the one hand we have the noble Au back-reflector and on the other hand, the refractory metal Ni. The incoming field is mostly dissipated in the sinusoidal Ni nanowire. This is due to the facts that (i) Ni exhibits a larger skin depth in the frequencies under consideration, dNi∼35\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
